GOOD PRACTICES AND INSPIRATION

A list of some Gnome applications written in Python:
+ pitivi (movie editor):                              https://git.gnome.org/browse/pitivi/
+ gtweak (customize advanced GNOME 3 options):        https://git.gnome.org/browse/gnome-tweak-tool/
+ gnome-music (music player):                         https://git.gnome.org/browse/gnome-music/
+ meld (compare files):                               https://git.gnome.org/browse/meld/
- pybliographer (bibliography Manager):               https://git.gnome.org/browse/pybliographer/
- postr (a simple Flickr uploader for GNOME):         https://git.gnome.org/browse/postr/
- orca (screen reader for individuals who are blind): https://git.gnome.org/browse/orca/
- accerciser (interactive accessibility explorer):    https://git.gnome.org/browse/accerciser/
- pyclutter (python bindings for Clutter):            https://git.gnome.org/browse/pyclutter/

The full list (all programming languages): https://git.gnome.org/browse/
